On Mon, 2 Sep 2002 Javabus(-at-)aol.com wrote:

> We just picked up a 1978 bus engine used with tranny. To change the seals on 
> the push rod tubes do you have to remove the rocker assembly or can you slide 

yes you remove the rocker assembly

> it through, also if you have to remove the rocker assembly when done should 

yes you just slide it thru when the rocker assembly is removed

> we adjust the valves. If yes to adjusting the valves is it the same as solid 

yes you should probably adjust the valves

> lifters as for these hydraulic, thanks anyone

no the lifters are adjusted completely differently, read it in Bentley but
basically turn the lifter in until it touches the pushrod, then take an
additional (officially) 2 turns in tighter to preload the hyd cam
followers, most people take 1-1.5 turns.  

easy job, use the newer viton seals on the pushrod tubes

Bob


